trans-unit.source: Navigate to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.developers.google.com/project), sign in with your Google account credentials.
trans-unit.target: Navigate to the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.developers.google.com/project), sign in with your Google account credentials.

trans-unit.source: Click **Create Project**, type a project name, then click **Create**.
trans-unit.target: Click **Create Project**, type a project name, then click **Create**.

trans-unit.source: If requested, carry out the SMS Verification, and click **Create** again.
trans-unit.target: If requested, carry out the SMS Verification, and click **Create** again.

trans-unit.source: Type in your new **Project name** and click **Create project**.
trans-unit.target: Type in your new **Project name** and click **Create project**.

trans-unit.source: Make a note of the project number in the **Projects** section.
trans-unit.target: Make a note of the project number in the **Projects** section.

trans-unit.source: You will need to set this value as the *PROJECT_ID* variable in the client.
trans-unit.target: You will need to set this value as the *PROJECT_ID* variable in the client.

trans-unit.source: In the project dashboard, click **Use Google APIs** > **Cloud Messaging for Android**, then on the next page click **Enable API**.
trans-unit.target: In the project dashboard, click **Use Google APIs** > **Cloud Messaging for Android**, then on the next page click **Enable API**.

trans-unit.source: In the API Manager, Click **Credentials** > **Add Credential** > **API Key**.
trans-unit.target: In the API Manager, Click **Credentials** > **Add Credential** > **API Key**.

trans-unit.source: In **Create a new key**, click **Server key**, type a name for your key, then click **Create**.
trans-unit.target: In **Create a new key**, click **Server key**, type a name for your key, then click **Create**.

trans-unit.source: Make a note of the **API KEY** value.
trans-unit.target: Make a note of the **API KEY** value.

trans-unit.source: You will use this API key value to enable Azure to authenticate with GCM and send push notifications on behalf of your app.
trans-unit.target: You will use this API key value to enable Azure to authenticate with GCM and send push notifications on behalf of your app.
